  "prompt": "My driving license is lost. How do I apply for a new one?",
  "response": "To apply for a new driving license, you'll typically need to:\n\n1. Gather required documents:\n- Proof of identity (passport, birth certificate)\n- Proof of address\n- Existing license details (if possible)\n\n2. Visit your local Department of Motor Vehicles (DMV) or equivalent agency\n\n3. Complete a replacement license application form\n\n4. Pay the replacement fee (varies by location)\n\n5. Provide a photo and possibly take a new vision test\n\n6. In some cases, you might need to fill out a lost document declaration\n\nThe exact process can vary depending on your specific location, so I recommend:\n- Checking your state/region's DMV website\n- Calling your local DMV for precise instructions\n- Bringing multiple forms of identification\n\nWould you like me to help you find specific details for your area?",
